The code that uses it is pretty complex (go up two folders in my gitlab link for that), so here&#x27;s a minimal example of the full API:<p><pre><code>  cothread_t a, b;  //cothread_t is a typedef to void*
  int main() {
    a = co_active();  //get a handle to the main thread
    b = co_create(entrypoint, stacksize_in_bytes);
    printf(&quot;a&quot;);
    co_switch(b);
    printf(&quot;c&quot;);
    co_delete(b);  //no need to delete a
  }
  void entrypoint() {
    printf(&quot;b&quot;);
    co_switch(a);
  }
  //output: &quot;abc&quot;
</code></pre>
We&#x27;ve only been using it in emulators so far. It&#x27;s in MESS, higan, twoMbit and a few others.
